    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of medium-sized European birch, typically reaching 15-25 m tall with a slender trunk and a crown of drooping branches and small, sharp-pointed leaves about 6 cm (2 inches) long. The bark is white, often with black diamond-shaped marks or larger patches at the base.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
